## Purpose

Adds ACOS-controlled mode so external OpenClaw can be run as an ACOS-governed execution surface instead of an unmanaged autonomous assistant.

Required note: OPENCLAW_ACOS_CONTROLLED=1 is opt-in. Existing OpenClaw behavior remains unchanged unless controlled mode is enabled.

## Entry points guarded

- Local agent execution through the agent command boundary.
- Gateway agent execution and Gateway protocol agent params.
- Channel dispatch turns, including Telegram-style inbound dispatch.
- Cron-created agent turns and isolated cron agent execution.

## Dangerous tools guarded

- Shell execution through exec tool defaults.
- apply_patch execution.
- Dangerous action classes now require ACOS approval metadata when controlled mode is enabled.

## Controlled-mode behavior

When OPENCLAW_ACOS_CONTROLLED=1 or OPENCLAW_DISABLE_AUTONOMOUS_INTAKE=1 is set, unmanaged mutating agent execution is rejected unless valid ACOS provenance is present. Diagnostic mode remains limited to non-mutating checks.

## Provenance validator purity change

src/acos/provenance.ts is a pure leaf module. It does not import gateway, channel, cron, shell, repo, logging, config runtime, infra/env, or package alias modules. Local minimal env flag parsing is implemented inside the module.

## Validation passed

- node --import tsx provenance import check: passed.
- Minimal in-repo Vitest config for src/acos/provenance.test.ts: 11 passed.
- node_modules/.bin/oxfmt --write --threads=1 on changed TS files: passed.
- node_modules/.bin/oxlint --tsconfig config/tsconfig/oxlint.core.json on changed TS files: passed.
- Targeted containment import checks: passed.

## Normal Vitest status

- node scripts/run-vitest.mjs run src/acos/provenance.test.ts: passed, 1 file / 11 tests.

## Remaining bypass risks

- Controlled mode is opt-in and requires OpenClaw processes to be started with the controlled-mode environment flag.
- ACOS provenance is metadata-based; it is not cryptographically signed in this patch.
- Existing processes already running without controlled mode are not retroactively contained.
- External sends outside the guarded agent/channel/tool paths were not exhaustively redesigned in this patch.

## Safe operating rule

Run OpenClaw as an ACOS subordinate only with OPENCLAW_ACOS_CONTROLLED=1 enabled and ACOS-issued provenance supplied for mutating or agent-execution paths.

## Merge condition

Ready to merge after reviewer acceptance and CI confirmation.

## Real behavior proof

After-fix evidence from the local OpenClaw setup on branch `codex/acos-openclaw-containment`:

```text
$ node --import tsx -e "import('./src/acos/provenance.ts').then(() => console.log('provenance import ok'))"
provenance import ok

$ node scripts/run-vitest.mjs run src/acos/provenance.test.ts
Test Files  1 passed (1)
Tests       11 passed (11)

$ node scripts/run-vitest.mjs run --config test/vitest/vitest.gateway-methods.config.ts
Test Files  55 passed (55)
Tests       1075 passed (1075)

$ node scripts/run-vitest.mjs run --config test/vitest/vitest.bundled.config.ts
Test Files  2 passed (2)
Tests       167 passed (167)

$ node_modules/.bin/oxlint --tsconfig config/tsconfig/oxlint.core.json ...changed TS files
Found 0 warnings and 0 errors.

$ node --import tsx scripts/protocol-gen.ts && node --import tsx scripts/protocol-gen-swift.ts
wrote dist/protocol.schema.json
wrote apps/shared/OpenClawKit/Sources/OpenClawProtocol/GatewayModels.swift
```

The protocol generator produced the committed Swift artifact update for `AgentParams.acosProvenance` and `AgentParams.diagnosticMode`.


## Real behavior proof

**Behavior or issue addressed:** ACOS containment for OpenClaw controlled mode. With `OPENCLAW_ACOS_CONTROLLED=1`, unmanaged local/Gateway agent execution and Telegram-channel dispatch are rejected unless ACOS task provenance is present. Dangerous tool classes require ACOS approval metadata. Valid ACOS provenance is accepted by the guard.

**Real environment tested:** Local OpenClaw checkout at PR head `570c8084b3` in `/Users/openclaw/workspace/openclaw`, running Node/Vitest from the repository `node_modules`. No ACOS repo was modified. No Pompa repo was inspected. Telegram token availability was checked only as a boolean and no token, chat id, username, or private identifier was printed.

**Exact steps or command run after this patch:**

```sh
GIT_HEAD_FOR_PROOF=$(git rev-parse --short HEAD) OPENCLAW_ACOS_CONTROLLED=1 node --import tsx <<'JS'
import { runPreparedChannelTurn } from './src/channels/turn/kernel.ts';
import {
  ACOS_APPROVAL_REJECTION_MESSAGE,
  ACOS_CONTROLLED_REJECTION_MESSAGE,
  ACOS_DIAGNOSTIC_REJECTION_MESSAGE,
  assertAcosControlledActionAllowed,
} from './src/acos/provenance.ts';

const env = {
  ...process.env,
  OPENCLAW_ACOS_CONTROLLED: '1',
  OPENCLAW_DISABLE_AUTONOMOUS_INTAKE: undefined,
  OPENCLAW_ACOS_PROVENANCE: undefined,
  OPENCLAW_ACOS_DIAGNOSTIC_MODE: undefined,
};
const valid = {
  acos_dispatch: true,
  dispatcher: 'acos',
  acos_task_id: 'task-redacted-001',
  run_id: 'run-redacted-001',
  queue_id: 'queue-redacted-001',
  dispatched_at: '2026-06-06T00:00:00.000Z',
};
const approved = {
  ...valid,
  approval_granted: true,
  approval_scope: ['shell_exec', 'apply_patch'],
};

console.log('environment: local OpenClaw checkout, head=' + process.env.GIT_HEAD_FOR_PROOF);
console.log('controlled mode env:', process.env.OPENCLAW_ACOS_CONTROLLED);
console.log('telegram env token present:', process.env.TELEGRAM_BOT_TOKEN ? 'yes' : 'no');

for (const action of ['agent_turn', 'gateway_agent_turn']) {
  try {
    assertAcosControlledActionAllowed({ action, env, mutating: true });
    console.log(action + ' unmanaged rejection: FAILED');
  } catch (error) {
    console.log(action + ' unmanaged rejection:', error.message);
  }
}

try {
  assertAcosControlledActionAllowed({ action: 'agent_turn', env, diagnosticMode: true, mutating: true });
  console.log('diagnostic mutating rejection: FAILED');
} catch (error) {
  console.log('diagnostic mutating rejection:', error.message);
}

let recordCalled = false;
let dispatchCalled = false;
try {
  await runPreparedChannelTurn({
    channel: 'telegram',
    routeSessionKey: 'agent:main:telegram:redacted-peer',
    storePath: '/tmp/openclaw-redacted-sessions.json',
    ctxPayload: {
      Body: '[redacted benign Telegram message]',
      From: '[redacted-chat-id]',
      To: '[redacted-bot-id]',
      MessageSid: '[redacted-message-id]',
      SessionKey: 'agent:main:telegram:redacted-peer',
      CommandAuthorized: false,
    },
    recordInboundSession: async () => { recordCalled = true; },
    runDispatch: async () => { dispatchCalled = true; return {}; },
    admission: { kind: 'dispatch' },
  });
  console.log('telegram dispatch rejection: FAILED');
} catch (error) {
  console.log('telegram dispatch rejection:', error.message);
  console.log('telegram recordInboundSession called:', recordCalled);
  console.log('telegram runDispatch called:', dispatchCalled);
}

try {
  assertAcosControlledActionAllowed({ action: 'shell_exec', env, mutating: true, requiresApproval: true, provenance: valid });
  console.log('shell_exec without approval: FAILED');
} catch (error) {
  console.log('shell_exec without approval:', error.message);
}

try {
  assertAcosControlledActionAllowed({ action: 'apply_patch', env, mutating: true, requiresApproval: true, provenance: valid });
  console.log('apply_patch without approval: FAILED');
} catch (error) {
  console.log('apply_patch without approval:', error.message);
}

assertAcosControlledActionAllowed({ action: 'shell_exec', env, mutating: true, requiresApproval: true, provenance: approved });
console.log('shell_exec guard with approval metadata: accepted by guard logic; no shell command executed');

assertAcosControlledActionAllowed({ action: 'agent_turn', env, mutating: true, provenance: valid });
console.log('valid ACOS provenance for agent_turn: accepted');

console.log('expected messages:', ACOS_CONTROLLED_REJECTION_MESSAGE, '|', ACOS_APPROVAL_REJECTION_MESSAGE, '|', ACOS_DIAGNOSTIC_REJECTION_MESSAGE);
JS
```

**Evidence after fix:** Actual terminal output from the local OpenClaw setup:

```text
environment: local OpenClaw checkout, head=570c8084b3
controlled mode env: 1
telegram env token present: no
agent_turn unmanaged rejection: OpenClaw is running in ACOS-controlled mode. This action requires ACOS task provenance.
gateway_agent_turn unmanaged rejection: OpenClaw is running in ACOS-controlled mode. This action requires ACOS task provenance.
diagnostic mutating rejection: OpenClaw diagnostic mode is limited to non-mutating checks.
telegram dispatch rejection: OpenClaw is running in ACOS-controlled mode. This action requires ACOS task provenance.
telegram recordInboundSession called: false
telegram runDispatch called: false
shell_exec without approval: OpenClaw is running in ACOS-controlled mode. This action requires ACOS approval metadata.
apply_patch without approval: OpenClaw is running in ACOS-controlled mode. This action requires ACOS approval metadata.
shell_exec guard with approval metadata: accepted by guard logic; no shell command executed
valid ACOS provenance for agent_turn: accepted
expected messages: OpenClaw is running in ACOS-controlled mode. This action requires ACOS task provenance. | OpenClaw is running in ACOS-controlled mode. This action requires ACOS approval metadata. | OpenClaw diagnostic mode is limited to non-mutating checks.
```

Supplemental validation output from the same local setup:

```text
$ node scripts/run-vitest.mjs run src/acos/provenance.test.ts
Test Files  1 passed (1)
Tests       11 passed (11)

$ node scripts/test-projects.mjs test/vitest/vitest.gateway-methods.config.ts
Test Files  55 passed (55)
Tests       1075 passed (1075)

$ node scripts/run-vitest.mjs run --config test/vitest/vitest.bundled.config.ts
Test Files  2 passed (2)
Tests       167 passed (167)

$ OPENCLAW_OXLINT_SKIP_PREPARE=1 node scripts/run-oxlint.mjs --tsconfig config/tsconfig/oxlint.core.json --format github src ui packages
Found 0 warnings and 0 errors.

$ node --import tsx scripts/protocol-gen.ts && node --import tsx scripts/protocol-gen-swift.ts
wrote /Users/openclaw/workspace/openclaw/dist/protocol.schema.json
wrote /Users/openclaw/workspace/openclaw/apps/shared/OpenClawKit/Sources/OpenClawProtocol/GatewayModels.swift
```

**Observed result after fix:** Controlled mode rejected unmanaged local agent, Gateway agent, diagnostic mutating, Telegram-channel dispatch, shell-exec-without-approval, and apply-patch-without-approval paths before agent dispatch or dangerous action execution. The Telegram-channel dispatch proof used redacted Telegram-shaped inbound payload fields and showed `recordInboundSession` and `runDispatch` were both `false`, so no autonomous Telegram-originated agent work proceeded. Valid ACOS provenance and approval metadata were accepted by the guard logic without executing shell commands or applying patches.

**What was not tested:** Live external Telegram send was not attempted because this shell has no `TELEGRAM_BOT_TOKEN` available (`telegram env token present: no`), and secrets/private Telegram config were intentionally not inspected. No screenshots were attached. No destructive command, repository mutation, external send, live webhook, or Pompa/ACOS modification was performed.


### P1 security review after-fix evidence

The follow-up security fix gates ACOS control fields at the Gateway server boundary and makes diagnostic mode fail closed for mutating actions before provenance can allow the action.

Actual local validation after the P1 fix:

```text
$ node --import tsx -e "import('./src/acos/provenance.ts').then(() => console.log('provenance import ok'))"
provenance import ok

$ node scripts/run-vitest.mjs run src/acos/provenance.test.ts
Test Files  1 passed (1)
Tests       11 passed (11)

$ OPENCLAW_VITEST_MAX_WORKERS=2 NODE_OPTIONS=--max-old-space-size=8192 OPENCLAW_TEST_PROJECTS_PARALLEL=2 OPENCLAW_VITEST_SHARD_NAME=agentic-gateway-methods node scripts/test-projects.mjs test/vitest/vitest.gateway-methods.config.ts
Test Files  55 passed (55)
Tests       1078 passed (1078)

$ OPENCLAW_OXLINT_SKIP_PREPARE=1 node scripts/run-oxlint.mjs --tsconfig config/tsconfig/oxlint.core.json --format github src ui packages
Found 0 warnings and 0 errors.

$ node scripts/run-vitest.mjs run --config test/vitest/vitest.bundled.config.ts
Test Files  2 passed (2)
Tests       167 passed (167)
```

Security behaviors covered by the updated tests:

- Public Gateway callers sending self-shaped `acosProvenance` and `diagnosticMode` have those fields stripped before agent execution, so public callers cannot spoof ACOS provenance to bypass controlled mode.
- Trusted Gateway callers, limited to backend-mode clients or admin-scoped clients, can still forward valid ACOS provenance and diagnostic mode for control-plane execution.
- `diagnosticMode=true` with valid ACOS provenance and `mutating=true` is rejected with `OpenClaw diagnostic mode is limited to non-mutating checks.`

No live Telegram send, secret inspection, ACOS modification, Pompa inspection, destructive command, repo mutation, external send, or protocol schema update was performed for this P1 fix.

